## Change Log

### 2026-03-01
- **Objective**: Implement multi-model LLM support for performance insights
- **Rationale**: Enable users to choose between different LLM providers (Mistral, OpenAI) for flexibility and cost optimization
- **Impact**: LLM integration layer, provider interface, CLI commands, core pipeline
- **Changes**:
  - Created `internal/llm/provider.go` with Provider interface and factory pattern
  - Implemented `internal/llm/mistral.go` for Mistral API client
  - Implemented `internal/llm/openai.go` for OpenAI API client
  - Updated `internal/llm/insights.go` to use provider interface with error handling
  - Enhanced `internal/core/pipeline.go` with provider-based LLM configuration
  - Updated CLI commands to support `--llm-provider` flag for provider selection
  - Added environment variable support for both MISTRAL_API_KEY and OPENAI_API_KEY
  - Created comprehensive tests for provider creation and validation
- **Testing**: Unit tests for provider creation, integration tests for multi-model functionality
- **Result**: Users can now select LLM providers via CLI flags, with proper error handling and fallback mechanisms

### 2026-03-01
- **Objective**: Implement advanced plugin management UI with marketplace and update functionality
- **Rationale**: Enhance plugin system usability and provide centralized plugin discovery/management
- **Impact**: Web UI, server endpoints, plugin management workflow
- **Changes**:
  - Created interactive plugin marketplace UI with install/update/uninstall capabilities
  - Implemented visual plugin capability matrix for easy comparison between plugins
  - Added plugin health monitoring with real-time status indicators
  - Enhanced plugin list with search, filtering, and detailed plugin information
  - Added server endpoints: `/plugins/marketplace`, `/plugins/install`, `/plugins/update`, `/plugins/uninstall`
  - Updated JavaScript to use real server endpoints instead of simulated functions
  - Added comprehensive error handling and user feedback for plugin operations
  - Created unit tests for new server endpoints
- **Testing**: Unit tests for marketplace and plugin management endpoints, manual UI testing
- **Result**: Users can now discover, install, update, and manage plugins through an intuitive web interface with real-time feedback

### 2026-03-01
- **Objective**: Implement Enhanced Real-Time Monitoring Dashboard with performance trends and comparative analysis
- **Rationale**: Provide comprehensive performance monitoring with historical data, trends, and comparative analysis for better decision making
- **Impact**: WebSocket server, web UI, performance tracking, data analysis
- **Changes**:
  - Enhanced WebSocket server with performance history tracking using `PerformanceSnapshot` struct
  - Added `performanceHistory` array with thread-safe access via mutex
  - Implemented `recordPerformanceSnapshot()` method to capture metrics on each data update
  - Added `GetPerformanceHistory()` and `getPerformanceHistory()` methods for data access
  - Created performance analysis endpoints: `/performance/history` and `/performance/analysis`
  - Implemented trend analysis with `analyzePerformanceTrends()` and `calculatePerformanceTrends()` methods
  - Added improvement potential calculation with `calculateImprovementPotential()` function
  - Enhanced web UI with comprehensive metrics dashboard showing performance score, critical/high issues, and trends
  - Added performance trends visualization with line charts for score and issue resolution over time
  - Implemented comparative analysis with baseline vs current comparison charts
  - Added score breakdown visualization with doughnut chart and category distribution with polar area chart
  - Updated JavaScript to handle WebSocket messages with performance history data
  - Added CSS styles for new dashboard components with dark mode support
  - Created test dashboard HTML file for component verification
  - Added comprehensive unit tests for performance history functionality
- **Testing**: Unit tests for performance history tracking, analysis endpoints, and snapshot limits
- **Result**: Users now have access to comprehensive real-time monitoring with historical trends, comparative analysis, and visual breakdowns of performance metrics, enabling better performance optimization decisions